{
  "text": "Some channel ordering algorithms can be applied to improve the performance. We find that even a simple sorted QR decomposition (SQRD) improves the performance significantly. The SQRD algorithm reorders the sequence of detection to minimize the risk of error propagation, by maximizing |R i,i | for i = N t \u2212 1, N t \u2212 2, . . . , 0 [CITATION_1] . Therefore the transmit antennas with strongest signal is assigned to the levels closer to the root of the tree [CITATION_2] .",
